name: Pura Gunung Kawi Parking Lot
address: Tampaksiring, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: The 10th temple, the other side of the beauty of Mount Kawi. An extraordinary work made by humans hundreds of years ago. Visit for the umpteenth time on August 22, 2023, to see and enjoy a masterpiece in the 10th temple complex. You must visit when visiting the Tampaksiring area, Ubud and its surroundings.
review 2: If you are on Bali please do not miss this extraordinary place. Amazing piece of history and a wonderful experience. To note, plenty of steps.
review 3: Great art stone wall creation with beautiful landscape
review 4: Do not park here with bike and consider other location for your car. They will try to charge 5000 parking fee. Tourist scam.
review 5: Historical site from Bali Ancestors during kingdom period

name: Waroeng Podjok GK
address: Jl. Bayu Suta No.73, Tampaksiring, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: Great food! Located near the temple and I thought it was reasonably priced 22k for the Chinese chicken pancakes and 10K for a Diet Coke. She does have a restroom but I recommend you use the one in Temple Park. Wonderful people
review 2: Delicious coffee and great service. Mie goreng was one of the best we have had. Cold coconut was also refreshing. The prices are great. The only thing was that we were not able to pay by card.
review 3: Food is cheap and amazing, staff are very nice. Very well located right by the temple as well. Just think of this place as you struggle back up the steps to leave the temple
review 4: Highly recommended place, the food is super tasty and delicious,  love the fried rice so much. They have a free wifi , you can ask the password to the owner, they're so nice and friendly.
review 5: Best satay i had in Bali, would definetely recommend this place

review 1: Decent fried chicken in the middle of no where.
review 3: Like any other ACK, it's pretty good.
review 4: Cheap fried chicken with good taste.

name: Kafe Kawi
address: Objek Pura Gunung Kawi, Jalan Werkudara, No. 1, Tampaksiring, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: Tiny cafe, had an Ice latte here, in the morning very quiet place with only serene sounds of birds and wind. Wonderful place to grab a coffee before or after visiting the temple
review 2: Kafe Kawi hands down best views. The food is good. The juices are good and the fried bananas the best. The staff is really nice and the place is just a great location. The kafe has a resident cat, born in the temple and now looked after really well by the kafe staff, Sita is her name and she is really sweet.
review 3: Favorite place!! We decided to have lunch before exploring the temple nearby and it was awesome. The sky was clear and we enjoyed our meals with a view on Mt. Agung, the highest mountain on Bali. Prices were not expensive at all.
review 4: Incredible view, very good noodles, great coffee and pretty good apple pie. Super friendly staff
review 5: We tried a vegetarian nasi campur and it was excellent. The staff is very friendly and the view with mount Agung is beautiful.

name: Warung Makan Ulam Carik
address: H8C5+92W, Jl. Dr. Ir. Soekarno, Tampaksiring, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: Although not particularly welcoming, the food was delivered quickly and we enjoyed it. We had the fried noodles and sayur hijau which were both delicious. The restaurant was clean and cool.
review 2:
Great food, great prices!!
Wife and daughter enjoyed it, terimah kasi.
review 3: Great foods made by mom and daughter. When you are traveling to watch volcanos in Bali best place for lunch
review 4: The food is good and at good prices. The owners are very honest and polite. Recommend!
review 5: Simple warung with local cost friendly food

review 2: Must try delicious local food and cheap
review 3: Delicious Food and super friendly staff. Thank you for having us.
review 4: One of the place to grab Balinese dish in Tampaksiring, taste good cheap price
review 5: The cuisine very delicious...this is true Bali even not Halal

review 2: The chili really goods in here, I like it.

name: Remy Homestay
address: Tampaksiring, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: We spent our last days in Bali staying in Remy's Homestay and we had a wonderful time. The village is beautiful and is so close to Ubud and to everything around to explore! I recommend it to anyone who wants to stay a bit far from the tourists and wants to enjoy the Balinese culture. Remy's family is beautiful and they provide a good service!
review 2:
We had a really good time there. The village is a must see. You can go to be blessed by water and see one of the most beautiful temple I've ever seen . All that just by walk.
All around the streets Ogoh Ogoh the demon big statues are amazing to see.

Remy and is family are just careful enough to make your trip authentic and learn about the culture while you LL still have your privacy.

Definitely recommend this place for anyone who wanna enjoy an authentic travel.

If you want a luxury place maybe search for something else. You'll find there all you need good bed, hot water, good toilet even tv in your room, all that in a simple way.
review 3: I stay at Remy Homestay often frendly staff good atmosphere and enjoy there hospitality

name: Green Carik
address: Jl. Gn. Kawi, Tampaksiring, Kec. Tampaksiring, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80552, Indonesia
review 1: It‚Äôs a great place to have a rest a bit if you are visiting Gunung Kawi Temple. Not for only enjoying the foods and drinks, but you could also take a swing and zip-line (flying fox) adventure, having the best time with the view of the rice-field landscapeü§©
review 2: We did the Zipline and treetop trekking course here and it was a wonderful experience! Set among rice terraces and jungle, this was the most beautiful place for a Zipline. The equipment was safe and my kids were taken care of so well by the staff. Adults and children loved this Zipline. So much fun and stunning photographs. It was a dramatic way to get down to the Gunung Kawi Temples. Highly recommended!
review 3: The view was very nice but im so disappointed about the food .you will get small portion of chicken üòÇ so the food was disappointing but the place was very nice tho
review 4: Disappointing size of food(micro chicken) and price. Rice is a small cap.. drinks under average.
review 5: Nice place with good food and amazing view. I had a chicken with peanut sauce and local ice cream

review 2: I love the ice coffe from kakiang and the cake.. üòçüòç
